                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18281204-258-off1363 t18281204-258-victim2217"></join>
                  </persName>
               
            .</p>
               <p>DAVID SAGE. I am a <rs id="t18281204-258-viclabel1365" type="occupation">builder</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18281204-258-victim2217 t18281204-258-viclabel1365"></join>. I lost some wood, and a shovel, last Thursday, from a field where I am building; I did not see them taken - but I had been robbed before, and set a man to watch; these are the articles.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18281204-258-person2218">
                  THOMAS 
                  SAGE
               <interp inst="t18281204-258-person2218" type="surname" value="SAGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18281204-258-person2218" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18281204-258-person2218" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was desired to watch in the field, where there is a house in an unfinished state; it is called Stone-field, near White Conduit-house. About half-past eight o'clock in the morning, I saw the prisoner come into the field, and go into a cottage; she then came out, and took four pieces of wood - she then took the shovel out of the cottage; she came out with this wood and the shovel; when she got about one hundred yards, I took her with them.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18281204-258-person2219">
                  JAMES 
                  GRIFFITHS
               <interp inst="t18281204-258-person2219" type="surname" value="GRIFFITHS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18281204-258-person2219" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18281204-258-person2219" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a bricklayer's labourer. This shovel is mine; it was in the house that is building for Mr. Sage.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18281204-258-person2220">
                  GEORGE 
                  UPWARD
               <interp inst="t18281204-258-person2220" type="surname" value="UPWARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18281204-258-person2220" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18281204-258-person2220" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I took the prisoner: she said she hoped Mr. Sage would not be severe with her.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was coming from work - this young man seized me, and said, "I am looking out for you;" I said, "For what?" he said, "You want to steal that wood over the way:" I said, "No, I don't want to take it."</p>
               <p>GUILTY. Aged 38.</p>


